  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To evaluate the polysomnographic performance of an automatic ventilatory mode compared with
      the gold standard (manual polysomnographic titration) to adjust chronic non-invasive
      ventilation by means of a randomized cross-over study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Prospective randomized crossover study in 26 patients with chronic non-invasive ventilation
      (NIV) criteria, comparing the NIV titration with polysomnography vs an automatic mode of
      ventilation. It will be compared with clinical parameters of ventilation, blood analysis and
      inflammation reactants as well as evaluating the patient's comfort after each mode.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
